# Tailwind CSS (Scoped Notes)

## Context

- When working on Tailwind styling in this repo.

## Requirements

- Follow the repo’s existing Tailwind major version; do not migrate versions opportunistically.
- If the repo uses Tailwind v4, prefer CSS-first configuration (`@theme`) and `@import "tailwindcss";`.
- If the repo uses Tailwind v3, keep `@tailwind base/components/utilities` and existing config structure.
- Follow the repo’s existing PostCSS/Vite integration rather than changing build tooling opportunistically.
- Keep UI consistent with existing component patterns and dark mode usage.

## Examples

<example>
```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --spacing: 0.25rem;
  --radius-lg: 0.75rem;
}
```
</example>

<example type="invalid">
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities; /* v4 projects generally use @import "tailwindcss" */
```
</example>
